code:
Vieta's formula states that for a cubic of the form $ax^3 + bx^2 + cx + d,$ the sum of the roots is $-b/a.$ We have that
\begin{align*}
p+q+r &= -\frac{-50}{30} = \frac{5}{3}.
\end{align*}
In this scenario we see that all variables:
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{1-p} +\frac{1}{1-q} +\frac{1}{1-r} 
&= \frac{(1-q)(1-r) + (1-p)(1-r)+(1-p)(1-q)}{(1-p)(1-q)(1-r)} \\
&= \frac{3-(p+q+r)+(pq+qr+pr)-pqr}{(1-p)(1-q)(1-r)}
\end{align*}
By Vieta's formulas, we know that $(pq+qr+pr) = \frac{22}{30},$ $pqr = \frac{1}{30},$ and $p + q + r = \frac{5}{3}.$ We obtain
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{1-p} +\frac{1}{1-q} +\frac{1}{1-r} &= \frac{3-\frac{5}{3} + \frac{22}{30} - \frac{1}{30}}{\left(1-p\right)\left(1-q\right)\left(1-r\right)}
\end{align*}
Therefore,
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{1-p} +\frac{1}{1-q} +\frac{1}{1-r} &= \frac{9-\frac{5}{1}}{-\left(p+q+r-2\right)pq}\\
&= \frac{9-\frac{5}{1}}{-\frac{7}{3}pq}\\
&= \frac{\frac{24}{1}}{-\frac{7}{3}pq}\\
&=\frac{\frac{24}{1}}{-\frac{7}{3}(\frac{1}{30})}\\
&= \frac{\frac{24}{1}\times \frac{3}{1}\times\frac{30}{7}}
{-\frac{1}{30} \times 7 }\\
&=\frac{\frac{24}{1} \times \frac{3}{1} \times \frac{30}{7}}{-7 \times  (\frac{1}{30}) } \\
&= \frac{\frac{24 \times 30 \times 3}{1}}{-7 \times  \frac{1}{30} } \\
&=\frac{\frac{30 \times 6 \times 3 \times 30}{1}}{\frac{-7}{30} }\\
&=\frac{\frac{4 \times 5  \times 6 \times 3  \times 10}{1}}{-\frac{7}{30} }  \\
&=\frac{\frac{4  \times 2 \times  5  \times 3  \times 10}{1}       }{\frac{-7}{30} } \\
&= \frac{-\frac{4   \times  2  \times  5 \times 3 \times  10   }{  1 }    }{\frac{-7}{30} }       \\
&=\frac{4 \times \frac{2 \times 5 \times 3 \times 10}{-1}}{\frac{-7}{30}}\\
&= \frac{\frac{-240}{1}}{-\frac{7}{30}}\\
&= \frac{\frac{240}{-1}}{-\frac{7}{30}}\\
&=\frac{\frac{240}{-1} \times \frac{-30}{-7}}{-\frac{7}{30}}\\
&=  \frac{-30 \times 240}{-1 \times -7}\\
&=\frac{30 \times 240}{ -(-7)}   \\
&= \boxed{ \frac{7200}{7}  }
\end{align*}
Therefore, the sum is $\frac{7200}{7}.$

